    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="592"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1010.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Mexican Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Memorandum—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>The Embassy of Mexico respectfully draws the Department of State’s attention to
                    the propriety of inflicting condign punishment on three men belonging to a band
                    which crossed the boundary line and attacked Saric and other places in Sonora,
                    and whose case is to be heard to-day in the county court of Nogales, Ariz., to
                    which end the said embassy begs that appropriate instructions be issued to
                    District Attorney Morrison.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexican Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
